{
  "stem": "4289.2",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They were not used to that climate.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So my stepmother, she went to her uncle and begged him for help.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And he gave her some kind of an apartment adjoined to his factory of ice.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And they, they got to live in Tel Aviv.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But there was no room for me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "My stepmother said, look how small this is.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "You cannot live here.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "If she would be my real mother she would say, lay down here on the floor with me.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "But she already rejected me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And I had no place, but still with my aunt.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And at that time, that was after the Sinai War, people in Israel had to have special stamps to get food.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I didn't have yet the stamps.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So my Aunt Esther, she was giving me the food of her children, really.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Sharing.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I felt that I am such a burden on them.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I went every day to Sochnut and asked them about, can I go to a kibbutz?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Can I go to a place to learn Hebrew?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And everybody told me I should go to an ulpan.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And one day, they told me yes, there is space in a kibbutz Geva, and you can go there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I took all my possessions, whatever I had, that were not good for summer in Israel.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I went to kibbutz Geva.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Over there I met a lot of my friends from my school, children from Egypt, children from Turkey, from Iraq, Iran.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was amazing to me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I didn't know there are Jews somewhere else.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The most shocking to me was Jews from India, that they looked Indian.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were yelling, you don't look Jewish.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I was saying, you don't look Jewish.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But we were all Jews.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I did.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
